Job Description:
Jumpgate Solutions is a software engineering firm that focuses on software as a service and onshore remote development. The mission of Jumpgate Solutions is to commercialize innovative technology product offerings such as eco-system management and support our client’s custom software development needs using an onshore remote development center. Jumpgate Solutions is key component of a broader portfolio of solution providers which includes Optimity Advisors LLC and SaltFlats LLC.


 PURPOSE
 We are hiring a Front-end Software Engineer to lead our software development team using the latest technologies to develop enterprise solutions for our customers. We need someone with both a broad set of experiences and skills as well as someone well versed in these technologies to lead future junior level developers. We look for developers who are experimenters and cross-functional. A person who is well versed in cloud technologies and SaaS would be ideal for this position.


 RESPONSIBILITIES

Apply Agile engineering best practices and principles;


Ability to develop technical requirements, architecture, and engineering documentation;
Ability to develop front-end website requirements, architecture, and engineering documentation;
Design highly interactive and functional user interfaces;
Ensure cross-platform optimization for mobile phones;
Help with code reviews and applying best practices;


Ensure responsiveness of applications;
Work alongside graphic designers for web design features;
Mentor junior developers through code reviews, paired programming, and collaborative conversation; and
Other duties assigned.



 Necessary Skills, Knowledge, and Abilities

Able to deploy solutions to appropriate environments using a CI/CD process;
Support clients through testing;
Experience creating, maintaining, and performing unit tests and other relevant automated testing;
Ability to create user interfaces and components that are modular, performant, and maintainable;
Able to integrate with RESTful APIs;


Familiarity with connecting services protected by OAuth/OpenID;
Familiarity with OAuth and the various supported flows;
Understanding of source control management systems and continuous deployment;
Ability to multitask, absorb new technologies, and work as both a team player contributor and a team a potential leader;
Strong organizational and project management skills;


Excellent verbal communication and client-facing experience;
Good problem-solving skills;
Self-driven, entrepreneurial, and strong team player; and
Willingness to work on legacy software.



 REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or closely related field;
5-7 years of experience as a software developer;
5 years combined experience with ALL of the following front-end languages, frameworks, and technologies: 

CSS3,
HTML5,
JavaScript, and
Typescript; 



5 years combined experience with 1 or more of the following: 

React,
Angular, and/or
JS; 



Experience building high-performance and scalable web services;
Experience with automated testing, agile development methodologies, debugging, and performance optimization;


Experience building and leading high-performance software development teams; and
Authorization to work in the United States on a permanent basis.



 PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS

Master’s degree in Computer Science or closely related field;


10 years of experience as a software developer;
Client-facing or consulting experience;
Experience developing in multiple tech stacks;
Experience with back-end development; and
Experience in mobile development, IOS, Android or both.



